{
  "description": "Redline /classify — Classifies AI agent tools into security roles (source, sink, guard, passthrough) and infers data-flow edges. Accepts a Config JSON via webhook, runs Claude Haiku for classification, returns a Graph JSON.",
  "version": 1,
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "classifier",
      "provider": "llm_anthropic",
      "name": "Tool Classifier (Claude Haiku)",
      "description": "Classifies each tool as source/sink/guard/passthrough, sets privileged flag, writes rationale, infers edges. Returns structured Graph JSON.",
      "config": {
        "profile": "claude-haiku-4-5",
        "apikey": "${ANTHROPIC_API_KEY}",
        "system_prompt": "You are a security classifier for AI agent tools. Given a list of tools (each with a name and description), classify each tool's role in the agent's data flow and infer edges between them.\n\n## Roles\n\n- **source**: Ingests untrusted external data (emails, URLs, webhooks, uploads). Entry points for prompt injection. Set `privileged: false`.\n- **sink**: Performs a privileged, potentially irreversible action (refunds, sending emails, deleting records). Set `privileged: true`.\n- **guard**: Safety check or approval gate (human approval, input validation, moderation). Set `privileged: false`.\n- **passthrough**: Internal operations with no direct security impact (searching records, formatting). Set `privileged: false`.\n\n## Rules\n\n1. Write a one-sentence `rationale` for each tool explaining WHY it has that role.\n2. For every source-sink pair, create an edge with `\"via\": \"context\"`.\n3. If a guard exists, route edges through it (source -> guard, guard -> sink without `via`).\n4. Normalize guard strings to `{ \"name\": \"<string>\", \"placement\": null }`.\n\n## Output\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON (no markdown, no explanation):\n```json\n{\n  \"nodes\": [{ \"id\": \"<tool_name>\", \"role\": \"source|sink|guard|passthrough\", \"privileged\": true|false, \"rationale\": \"<one sentence>\" }],\n  \"edges\": [{ \"from\": \"<id>\", \"via\": \"context\", \"to\": \"<id>\" }],\n  \"guards\": [{ \"name\": \"<name>\", \"placement\": \"<sink>|*|null\" }]\n}\n```",
        "claude-haiku-4-5": {
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_ANTHROPIC_KEY}"
        },
        "parameters": {
          "google": {}
        }
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 242,
          "y": 50.5
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "prompt_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "response_answers_1",
      "provider": "response_answers",
      "name": "Return Answers",
      "config": {
        "laneName": "answers",
        "name": "Return Answers"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 460,
          "y": 70
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "answers",
          "from": "classifier"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "chat_1",
      "provider": "chat",
      "name": "Chat",
      "config": {
        "hideForm": true,
        "mode": "Source",
        "parameters": {},
        "type": "chat",
        "name": "Chat"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": -290,
          "y": 60
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "prompt_1",
      "provider": "prompt",
      "name": "Prompt",
      "config": {
        "instructions": [
          "You are a security classifier for AI agent tools. Given a list of tools (each with a name and description), classify each tool's role in the agent's data flow and infer edges between them.  Roles Classify each tool into exactly one role:  source: Ingests untrusted external data (e.g., reading emails, fetching URLs, receiving webhooks, parsing uploads). These are entry points for prompt injection. sink: Performs a privileged, potentially irreversible action (e.g., issuing refunds, sending emails, deleting records, executing commands). Set privileged: true. guard: Acts as a safety check or approval gate (e.g., human approval, input validation, content moderation, allowlist checks). Set privileged: false. passthrough: Internal operations with no direct security impact (e.g., searching records, formatting data, logging). Set privileged: false. Rules A tool is a source if it reads from any channel an attacker could influence: email, URLs, webhooks, user messages, file uploads, API responses from third parties. A tool is a sink if it causes a real-world side effect that is hard to reverse: financial transactions, sending communications, modifying data, executing code, provisioning resources. A tool is a guard if its primary purpose is to check, validate, approve, moderate, or gate another action. Everything else is passthrough. For each tool, write a one-sentence rationale explaining WHY it has that role, referencing the tool's specific description. Edges Infer CAN_FLOW_INTO edges:  For every source-sink pair, create an edge with \"via\": \"context\" (data flows through the agent's shared context/prompt). If a guard exists, create edges from sources to the guard and from the guard to the sinks it protects (omit via for guard-to-sink edges). Guards Pass through any guards from the input config. Normalize strings to { \"name\": \"<string>\", \"placement\": null }. Objects keep their existing fields.  Output format Return ONLY valid JSON (no markdown, no explanation) matching this exact schema:  {   \"nodes\": [     { \"id\": \"<tool_name>\", \"role\": \"source|sink|guard|passthrough\", \"privileged\": true|false, \"rationale\": \"<one sentence>\" }   ],   \"edges\": [     { \"from\": \"<source_id>\", \"via\": \"context\", \"to\": \"<sink_id>\" }   ],   \"guards\": [     { \"name\": \"<guard_name>\", \"placement\": \"<sink_name>|*|null\" }   ] } Examples Input tools:  read_email: \"Read incoming customer emails\" issue_refund: \"Process a refund to the customer's payment method\" search_orders: \"Look up order history in the database\" Output:  {   \"nodes\": [     { \"id\": \"read_email\", \"role\": \"source\", \"privileged\": false, \"rationale\": \"Ingests untrusted external input from customer emails, which an attacker can craft.\" },     { \"id\": \"issue_refund\", \"role\": \"sink\", \"privileged\": true, \"rationale\": \"Performs an irreversible financial action by processing refunds.\" },     { \"id\": \"search_orders\", \"role\": \"passthrough\", \"privileged\": false, \"rationale\": \"Read-only database lookup with no external data ingestion or privileged side effect.\" }   ],   \"edges\": [     { \"from\": \"read_email\", \"via\": \"context\", \"to\": \"issue_refund\" }   ],   \"guards\": [] }"
        ],
        "name": "Prompt",
        "parameters": {
          "google": {}
        }
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": -20,
          "y": 40
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "chat_1"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "isLocked": false,
  "snapToGrid": true,
  "snapGridSize": [
    10,
    10
  ],
  "docRevision": 34,
  "project_id": "ce9f25a5-e907-487d-8ca7-ecc3671f6d7a"
}